Subject: [Caml-list] [ANN] tgls 0.8.2

Hello,

Since OpenGL 4.5 was announced on monday, I'd like to announce the release of tgls 0.8.2 which should be available shortly in opam.

It now provides support to program with OpenGL 4.5 and OpenGL ES 3.1. Full release notes:

https://github.com/dbuenzli/tgls/blob/master/CHANGES.md

Tgls is a set of independent OCaml libraries providing thin bindings to OpenGL Libraries. It has support for core OpenGL 3.{2,3} and 4.{0,1,2,3,4,5} and OpenGL ES 2 and 3.{0,1}.

Home page: http://erratique.ch/software/tgls

Best,

Daniel

P.S. The functions were not tested. There are 106 new entry points in OpenGL
4.5 and 68 in OpenGL ES 3.1.


